--- 
          flowchart TD
              id1(((Access Zerodha API from Angular App )))
              style id1 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:10px, font-size: 13px,padding-top: 4px
---
Crafted with :heart: by **gmanojisaac** • Follow on [GitHub](https://github.com/gmanoj.isaac)
--- 
        graph TD
            id1(Start)-->id2(1.Run Angular)
            style id1 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            style id2 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            id2(1.Run Angular) --> id3(Windows Env)
            
            id2(1.Run Angular) --> id4(NodeJs App)
            
            id2(1.Run Angular) --> id5(Angular with kiteConnectjs)
            
            id5(Angular with kiteConnectjs) --> id6(Access the instrument Quote)
            style id3 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            style id4 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            style id5 fill:orange,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        
            id5(Angular with kiteConnectjs) --> id7(Apply logic to generate signals)
            style id6 fill:orange,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            style id7 fill:orange,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        
            id7(Apply logic to generate signals) --> id8(Push the Triggers to Firebase)
        
            id8(Push the Triggers to Firebase)-->id9(Stop)
            style id8 fill:yellow,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
            style id9 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
--- ---
## Create a express Application by globally installing the generator ```typescript npm install -g express-generator ``` ## Scaffold a new Express application called myExpressApp by running # go to the new folder and execute npm install: ```typescript express myExpressApp --view pug npm install ``` # From a terminal in the Express application folder ```typescript npm start ``` # The official Javascript node client for communicating with the Kite Connect API. # Pay the Kite API Charges and activate it, use browser to generate the access code for the day ```typescript npm i kiteconnect https://kite.zerodha.com/connect/login?v=3&api_key=XXX ``` 
      graph TD
        id1(Create kc Object)-->id2(Valid 
 Access code)
        style id1 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        style id2 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        id1(Create kc Object) --> id3(Invalid 
 Access code)
        style id3 fill:cyan,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
--- 
        graph TD
          id1(Create kc Object)-->id2(Access code  
 Already created)
          style id1 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
          style id2 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
          id1(Create kc Object) --> id3(Access code  
 not created)
          style id3 fill:cyan,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
--- ---
## Create a Angular app ```typescript ng new kiteAngular ``` ## Create a new Repo and push the master # go to the new folder and execute npm install: ```typescript git remote remove origin git remote add origin https://github.com/gmanojisaac/AngularZerodha.git git remote -v show git status git log --oneline git add . git commit -am “Setup Github” git push -u origin master ``` # From a terminal in the Angular application folder ```typescript ng build ng serve ``` # The official Javascript node client for communicating with the Kite Connect API. # Pay the Kite API Charges and activate it, use browser to generate the access code for the day ```typescript npm i kiteconnect-ts https://kite.zerodha.com/connect/login?v=3&api_key=XXX ``` 
      graph TD
        id1(Create kiteTicker Object)-->id2(Add Valid Instruments)
        style id1 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        style id2 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        id2(Add Valid Instruments) --> id3(Ticker Connect)
        style id3 fill:cyan,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        id3(Ticker Connect) --> id4(Receive Ticks)
        style id4 fill:green,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
--- --- 
        graph TD
        id1(Start)-->id2(1.Get NSE Index Feed)
        style id1 fill:lightblue,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        style id2 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        id2(1.Get NSE Index Feed) --> id3(Calculate the flex point)
        
        id2(1.Get NSE Index Feed) --> id4(Populate the instrument array)
        
        id2(1.Get NSE Index Feed) --> id5(Generate the signals)
        
        id5(Generate the signals) --> id6(Push into Firebase Db)
        style id3 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        style id4 fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
        style id5 fill:orange,stroke:#333,stroke-width:4px
---
## Current working model --- 
        graph TD
          id1(Get the new Request Token from link) -->  id2(Delete the old Access code)
          id2(Delete the old Access code) --> id3(Run the nodeJS program and get the access token from log) 
          id3(Run the nodeJS program and get the access token from log)  --> id4(Copy the access token from log)
          id4(Copy the access token from log) --> id5(Program works correctly to get quote)
          id5(Program works correctly to get quote) --> id6(END)
## Write code for this --- 
        graph TD
          id1(2 min Sleep) -->  id2(Last sec-> Wake up for sleep Tracking)
          id2(Last sec-> Wake up for sleep Tracking) --> id3(Take Trade and 2 min sleep) 
          id3(Take Trade and 2 min sleep)  --> id4(Go into continuos Tracking with boundaries)
          id4(Go into continuos Tracking with boundaries) --> id5(Boundary breach take trade and 2 min sleep)
          id5(Boundary breach take trade and 2 min sleep) --> id5(Boundary breach take trade and 2 min sleep)
          id5(Boundary breach take trade and 2 min sleep) --> id6(Boundary breach on both sides no trade for day)
          id6(Boundary breach on both sides no trade for day) --> id7(END)
